# QA Automation Template (Pytest)

A general-purpose automation framework template designed for portfolio and real project use. It includes:

- Page Object Model structure for UI testing
- Shared fixtures and environment-driven config
- Allure reporting support
- Parallel execution with pytest-xdist
- A sample test suite for web and API
- CI workflow with GitHub Actions

## Tech Stack

- Python + pytest
- Selenium (web example)
- requests (API example)
- allure-pytest (reporting)
- pytest-xdist (parallel execution)

## Project Structure

```text
qa-automation-template/
  src/
    core/         # config, drivers, utilities
    pages/        # web page objects
    clients/      # API clients
    mobile/       # mobile placeholders
  tests/
    web/
    api/
    mobile/
  config/
  .github/workflows/
```

## Quick Start

1. Create and activate a virtual environment.
2. Install dependencies:

```bash
pip install -e .
```

3. Run all tests:

```bash
pytest
```

4. Run in parallel:

```bash
pytest -n auto
```

5. Generate Allure report (requires Allure CLI installed):

```bash
allure serve allure-results
```

## Environment Variables

- `BASE_URL` (default: `https://example.com`)
- `API_BASE_URL` (default: `https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com`)
- `BROWSER` (default: `chrome`)
- `HEADLESS` (`true` or `false`, default: `true`)

## Portfolio Tips

- Add real-world scenarios in `tests/` with clear markers (`smoke`, `regression`).
- Add test data factories and richer assertions.
- Add a `Makefile` or task runner scripts if desired.
- Include screenshots, flaky test handling, and failure artifacts.
